reviews.text:
Great venue, top, authentic food .
Will be a regular patron on my future trips to Hong Kong.
Just did a quick trip to HK in April and had to have a banquet at my favorite Indian restaurant.
Fantastic food as always, treated like a king by the staff and owners, impressed my guests as well.
Icy cold beer and plenty of great food.
Great place.  Cozy. Excellent food. Family friendly. Relaxing music and chilled vibe
I can visit this place every day. So so so much tasty food and high quality service. Owner is so much humble and welcoming. Ambiance is nice and they always play slow Indian music in background.

We had dinner the other day at this restaurant for the first time. What a luck, as once you enter you are welcomed, shown to a table with white linen and the menu is offered, with nice pictures with each food dish. The service is excellent and so is the food, served hot and so authentic. Highly recommended.
Excellent cuisine and wonderful service

result.name: Tong De Veggie

reviews.text: A good Asien vegetarian place with many different cuisines and a lot of fake meat options (including beyond meat). The mango sushi was absolutely brilliant. I did not enjoy the Tom Kha soup (the flavor was not there, the mix of "seafood" did not help). The "sweet and sour pork served in a whole pineapple" was really really good and very fresh, the "pork" was made out of amazing mushrooms, but it was not served in a pineapple. (Lost in translation? ^^)
Vegetarian food taste really good

Great little hidden veggie restaurant. Menus in English, price is reasonable, staff are very friendly. Food was delicious. I'm not usually a fan of mock meats but the sweet and sour 'pork' was great. Note that the address is #10 and you need to head into the lobby of the building and get a lift to the first floor.
Yummy vegetarian food and price is worthy

Good for locals. But not good for tourists if you’re after clean familiar food. Not too cheap either. Toilets were disgusting. Friendly staff. Really liked the Vietnamese Buns for starter. Wasted most of the other food.

reviews.text: 第一次去，點左個：黑松露芝士焗豬扒。味道唔錯，就系“豬扒”份量太多，我一個女仔食唔曬，唂住嘥嘢；另外，如果可以配上兩條青菜就更加好啦。環境同服務都幾好。👍

A good Asien vegetarian place with many different cuisines and a lot of fake meat options (including beyond meat). The mango sushi was absolutely brilliant. I did not enjoy the Tom Kha soup (the flavor was not there, the mix of "seafood" did not help). The "sweet and sour pork served in a whole pineapple" was really really good and very fresh, the "pork" was made out of amazing mushrooms, but it was not served in a pineapple. (Lost in translation? ^^)
魚生，椒鹽鮮魷 食都食得多 全部都係素真係第一次 香芒炸豆腐必點 考手功切出黎既係豆腐花 依間野值得一試
Pizza 絕對值得一試。炒飯亦都好食。

色香味俱全👍
